<font color="#FF0000">&quot;COOKIE'S DREAM&quot;</font><br>
<tt>Wed Dec  3 21:06:36 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
&quot;Cookie's Dream&quot;<br>
by <br>
Mustang Two Four<br><br>
This is a ballad of questionable sorts,<br>
a tragic tale of a jarhead Marine<br>
except for the stripe in his tight pink shorts<br>
he was shroud in nothing but green.<br><br>
He humped through the verdant hills<br>
shooting everything he caught in his sights<br>
He didn't register too many kills<br>
but he sure as hell lit up the boring nights.<br><br>
He hacked his way through thorny vines<br>
not able to follow the compass courses.<br>
And was rescued many, many, times<br>
By his friends in the Special Forces!<br><br>
But God smiled on his mangey, fiesty soul<br>
Never allowing him to be too badly hit.<br>
His guardian angel was tough and bold,<br>
A handsome, Special Forces...helicopter pilot!<br><br>
So, back in the land of the round eyes,<br>
he shuffles along from day to day.<br>
Often, one can hear his mournful cries...<br>
&quot;Gee, I wish I'd been a Green Beret!&quot;<br><br>
Humbly submitted by Captain Ramon, Omega Operation 1966.
